# 🔬 Comprehensive Code Review — Skin-Cancer-Detection

> **Reviewed**: All source code, scripts, configs, and tests
> **Date**: 2026-03-04
> **Perspectives**: Computer Vision • Data Science • ML Engineering • Python Patterns • Python Pro

---

## 📊 Project Overview

| Aspect | Details |
|--------|---------|
| **Task** | Binary skin lesion segmentation (ISIC 2018 Task 1) |
| **Models** | U-Net (SMP) + DeepLabV3 (torchvision MobileNetV3-Large) |
| **Loss** | Focal + Soft Dice (weighted combination) |
| **Metrics** | Dice Coefficient, IoU (macro-averaged) |
| **Training** | Mixed precision, warmup LR, DDP, resume support |
| **Inference** | TTA (hflip + vflip), threshold optimization |
| **Test Coverage** | 10 test files covering config, dataset, losses, metrics, trainer, distributed, evaluate |

---

## ✅ Strengths (What's Done Well)

### 🏗️ Architecture & Design
- **Clean separation of concerns**: `src/data/`, `src/models/`, `src/losses/`, `src/metrics/`, `src/training/`, `src/inference/`, `src/utils/` — textbook modular layout
- **Factory pattern** in [segmentation.py](file:///home/tontide1/coding/CV_project/Skin-Cancer-Detection/src/models/segmentation.py) with `_REGISTRY` makes adding new models straightforward
- **Config inheritance** (`_base_` + YAML merging) — excellent for experiment management with minimal repetition
- **CLI override system** with strict key validation prevents silent typos — very robust

### 🧠 ML Engineering
- **Differential learning rate** for encoder vs decoder — important for transfer learning
- **Warmup + ReduceOnPlateau/Cosine schedulers** — production-grade LR strategy
- **Resume-safe training**: saves `last_checkpoint.pth` every epoch with full optimizer/scaler/scheduler state
- **Best model tracking** with `ModelCheckpoint` + `EarlyStopping` — clean callback design
- **Checkpoint compatibility** via `load_state_dict_with_aux_compat` handles legacy aux head migration gracefully

### 🐍 Python Quality
- **`from __future__ import annotations`** consistently across all files — forward-compatible type hints
- **Type hints** on all public functions with proper return types
- **Comprehensive docstrings** with Args/Returns/Raises sections
- **`set_to_none=True`** in `optimizer.zero_grad()` — correct PyTorch 2.x best practice
- **Proper `GradScaler` API** using `torch.amp.GradScaler(device.type, ...)` — modern API usage

### 🔬 Computer Vision
- **Well-balanced augmentation pipeline**: spatial (flip, rotate, affine, elastic) + colour (brightness, HSV, blur, noise) + regularisation (CoarseDropout)
- **Resize before augmentation** — correct ordering
- **ImageNet normalization** applied consistently
- **TTA with geometric transforms** (hflip + vflip) — simple but effective
- **Threshold optimization** in evaluate.py searching [0.3, 0.7] — important for binary segmentation

### 🧪 Testing
- Good test coverage: config parsing, dataset pairing, losses (scalar/gradient/weighting), metrics (boundary cases), trainer resume, distributed context
- **Reference evaluation test** (`test_evaluate_streaming.py`) — excellent idea verifying streaming vs batch computation

